<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Ancient_sources">Ancient sources</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Yassa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Ancient sources"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><cite id="CITEREFBlakeFrye1949" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/Robert_Pierpont_Blake" title="Robert Pierpont Blake">Blake, Robert P.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Richard_N._Frye" title="Richard N. Frye">Frye, Richard N.</a> (1949). "History of the Nation of the Archers (The Mongols) by Grigor of Akancʻ; Hitherto Ascribed to Matakʻia The Monk: The Armenian Text Edited with an English Translation and Notes". <i>Harvard Journal of Asiatic Studies</i>. <b>12</b> (3–4): 269–443.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Harvard+Journal+of+Asiatic+Studies&amp;rft.atitle=History+of+the+Nation+of+the+Archers+%28The+Mongols%29+by+Grigor+of+Akanc%CA%BB%3B+Hitherto+Ascribed+to+Matak%CA%BBia+The+Monk%3A+The+Armenian+Text+Edited+with+an+English+Translation+and+Notes.&amp;rft.volume=12&amp;rft.issue=3%E2%80%934&amp;rft.pages=269-443&amp;rft.date=1949&amp;rft.aulast=Blake&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert+P.&amp;rft.au=Frye%2C+Richard+N.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AYassa" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Bar_Hebraeus" title="Bar Hebraeus">Bar Hebraeus</a> (Abul-Faraj) [13th century AD]. <i>Makhtbhanuth Zabhne (Chronicon)</i>  (vol. 2: <i>Chronicon Ecclesiasticum</i>) - The current edition of the Chronicon Ecclesiasticum is by Jean Baptiste Abbeloos and Thomas Joseph Lamy, Syriac text, Latin translation.</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFGibb1958" class="citation cs2">Gibb, H.A.R., ed. (1958), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/travels-of-ibn-battuta/The%20Travels%20of%20Ibn%20Battuta-1325%E2%80%931354-Volume-I/page/ii/mode/2up"><i>The Travels of Ibn Baṭṭūṭa, A.D. 1325–1354 (Volume 1)</i></a>, London: <a href="/wiki/Hakluyt_Society" title="Hakluyt Society">Hakluyt Society</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Travels+of+Ibn+Ba%E1%B9%AD%E1%B9%AD%C5%AB%E1%B9%ADa%2C+A.D.+1325%E2%80%931354+%28Volume+1%29&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Hakluyt+Society&amp;rft.date=1958&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Ftravels-of-ibn-battuta%2FThe%2520Travels%2520of%2520Ibn%2520Battuta-1325%25E2%2580%25931354-Volume-I%2Fpage%2Fii%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AYassa" class="Z3988"></span>.</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFGibb1962" class="citation cs2">Gibb, H.A.R., ed. (1962), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/travels-of-ibn-battuta/The%20Travels%20of%20Ibn%20Battuta-1325%E2%80%931354-Volume-II/page/ii/mode/2up"><i>The Travels of Ibn Baṭṭūṭa, A.D. 1325–1354 (Volume 2)</i></a>, London: Hakluyt Society</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Travels+of+Ibn+Ba%E1%B9%AD%E1%B9%AD%C5%AB%E1%B9%ADa%2C+A.D.+1325%E2%80%931354+%28Volume+2%29&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Hakluyt+Society&amp;rft.date=1962&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Ftravels-of-ibn-battuta%2FThe%2520Travels%2520of%2520Ibn%2520Battuta-1325%25E2%2580%25931354-Volume-II%2Fpage%2Fii%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AYassa" class="Z3988"></span>.</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFGibb1971" class="citation cs2">Gibb, H.A.R., ed. (1971), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/travels-of-ibn-battuta/The%20Travels%20of%20Ibn%20Battuta-1325%E2%80%931354-Volume-III/page/iii/mode/2up"><i>The Travels of Ibn Baṭṭūṭa, A.D. 1325–1354 (Volume 3)</i></a>, London: Hakluyt Society</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Travels+of+Ibn+Ba%E1%B9%AD%E1%B9%AD%C5%AB%E1%B9%ADa%2C+A.D.+1325%E2%80%931354+%28Volume+3%29&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Hakluyt+Society&amp;rft.date=1971&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Ftravels-of-ibn-battuta%2FThe%2520Travels%2520of%2520Ibn%2520Battuta-1325%25E2%2580%25931354-Volume-III%2Fpage%2Fiii%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AYassa" class="Z3988"></span>.</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFGibbBeckingham1994" class="citation cs2">Gibb, H.A.R.; Beckingham, C.F., eds. (1994), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/travels-of-ibn-battuta/The%20Travels%20of%20Ibn%20Battuta-1325%E2%80%931354-Volume-IV/page/ii/mode/2up"><i>The Travels of Ibn Baṭṭūṭa, A.D. 1325–1354 (Volume 4)</i></a>, London: Hakluyt Society, <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-904180-37-4" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-904180-37-4"><bdi>978-0-904180-37-4</bdi></a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Travels+of+Ibn+Ba%E1%B9%AD%E1%B9%AD%C5%AB%E1%B9%ADa%2C+A.D.+1325%E2%80%931354+%28Volume+4%29&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Hakluyt+Society&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-904180-37-4&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Ftravels-of-ibn-battuta%2FThe%2520Travels%2520of%2520Ibn%2520Battuta-1325%25E2%2580%25931354-Volume-IV%2Fpage%2Fii%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AYassa" class="Z3988"></span>. This volume was translated by Beckingham after Gibb's death in 1971. A separate index was published in 2000.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Vardan_Areveltsi" title="Vardan Areveltsi">Vardan Areveltsi</a> [13th century AD]. <i>Havakumn Patmutyun</i> (<i>Historical Compilation</i>). Currently preserved at the <a href="/wiki/Matenadaran" title="Matenadaran">Matenadaran</a> in <a href="/wiki/Yerevan" title="Yerevan">Yerevan</a>, Armenia.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Rash%C4%ABd_al-D%C4%ABn_%E1%B9%ACab%C4%ABb" class="mw-redirect" title="Rashīd al-Dīn Ṭabīb">Rashīd al-Dīn Ṭabīb</a> [<abbr title="circa">c.</abbr> 1306-1311 AD]. <i><a href="/wiki/Jami%27_al-tawarikh" title="Jami&#39; al-tawarikh">Jami' al-tawarikh</a> (Compendium of Chronicles).</i></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Ata-Malik_Juvayni" title="Ata-Malik Juvayni">Ata-Malik Juvayni</a> [13th century AD]. <i><a href="/wiki/Tarikh-i_Jahangushay" title="Tarikh-i Jahangushay">Tarikh-i Jahangushay</a> (History of the World Conqueror).</i></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Mirkhvand" title="Mirkhvand">Mirkhvand</a> [<abbr title="circa">c.</abbr>1497 AD]. <i><a href="/wiki/Raw%C5%BCat_a%E1%B9%A3-%E1%B9%A3af%C4%81%CA%BE" title="Rawżat aṣ-ṣafāʾ">Rawżat aṣ-ṣafāʾ</a> (The Gardens of purity in the biography of the prophets and kings and caliphs)</i>. Eng. trans. begun as History of the Early Kings of Persia, 1832.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Al-Maqrizi" title="Al-Maqrizi">al-Maqrizi</a> [<abbr title="circa">c.</abbr> 1442 AD]. <i>Kitāb al-Sulūk li-Ma'rifat Duwal al-Mulūk (The History of the Ayyubit and Mameluke Rulers)</i>. Translated (into French) by E. Quatremére (2 vols. Paris, 1837–1845)</li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Modern_sources">Modern sources</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Yassa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Modern sources"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><cite id="CITEREFAigle2004" class="citation journal cs1 cs1-prop-foreign-lang-source">Aigle, Denise (2004). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.cairn-int.info/journal-annales-2004-5-page-971.htm">"Mongolian Law versus Islamic Law: Between Myth and Reality"</a>. <i>Annales. Histoire, Sciences Sociales</i> (in French). <b>59</b> (5): 971–996. <a href="/wiki/ISSN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISSN (identifier)">ISSN</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/issn/2268-3763">2268-3763</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Annales.+Histoire%2C+Sciences+Sociales&amp;rft.atitle=Mongolian+Law+versus+Islamic+Law%3A+Between+Myth+and+Reality&amp;rft.volume=59&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=971-996&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.issn=2268-3763&amp;rft.aulast=Aigle&amp;rft.aufirst=Denise&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cairn-int.info%2Fjournal-annales-2004-5-page-971.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AYassa" class="Z3988"></span></li>
